script = ExtResource("3_g6gqd")
category = 15
text = "It is quite obvious that the Acedonian people are quite different than regular humans, not only by colour and height but by primal instincts and anatomy.

The average fresh adult in Acedonia is 7'2. Acedonians consider Adult age to be 25+ with elders being around 90 and above. Children are toddlers up until 8 years where they then go to their main schooling until the age of 20 where they take break for 2 years to figure out what to do and move on after. Despite the average 14 year old Acedonian being similar in mental capacity to a human 9 year old, they hold an impressive 5'7 at this age and have the strength of an average adult man. Male and Female Acedonians have very similar builds, with no difference in height or muscle capacity, only in mental attributes and reproductive systems. Acedonian elders never shrink, and despite averaging at 7'2 at 25 years old, they grow slightly until their 90s to which they incredibly slow down but do not stop. The average 60 year old Acedonian is 8'0 and 110 year old elder 8'8. Interestingly female Acedonians grow taller, but only once they become 90 years or older.

Anatomy is largely different to a human, especially to do with the blood. Acedonian blood cells are larger, to compromise for their size, as they need more oxygen. Their heart is also 30% larger than a humans and has an extra entry and exit valve for arteries and veins. This is needed to pump more blood to their bodies, but this adaptation also adds more potential growth in muscle than the average human does. Their muscles and skin are tougher than humans' are, and their legs are naturally more built with muscle to carry their astounding weight. 

Personality wise, female and male Acedonians are quite alike, with little differences. The differences comes between skin colours, where the Whites are usually more modest and blunt, the Blacks are more adamant and ambitious and the Reds are more cautious and plotting. There isnt really a war between White and Black people, and there never was. On the off-chance a Red child is born, they are also not scolded in the adult field, but often bullied during school due to children's immaturity to skin colour. Reds are much more likely to have Red offspring but it is not gurranteed. Two Red parents have the same chance to have a Red child like mixed parents don't. Meanwhile a mixed Red duo has only double the chance to have a Red child, meaning that finding them is rare. Families with Red Acedonians do have a lot of them, these are usually concentrated in certain towns or areas. There do exist many successful Red nobles and Kings, so the higher up the ladder you go, the less discrimination you see.

Acedonians are not known to have any intellectual differences to humans, but many researchers assume that they lose intelligence in basic thinking but gain IQ in battle. It is also unknown if Acedonians can use creator magic, but it is not out of the question. Acedonians were likely to have existed during the First Mans departure and they do feel the presense and strength of someone with a powerful Aura which they train subconciously through their powerful ambitions."
id = 9
name = "Acedonian People"
gdscript = ExtResource("1_5olqa")
